        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down. | Bromley. | Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>June 23<hi rend="superscript">d</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I thank you most sincerely for the great trouble, which you have taken in answering my questions.— Your answers are all perfectly clear &amp; distinct.— I am very glad indeed to hear of the case of the Sandpiper—<ref target="#foot.f1"/> such little facts are my delight. It will go well with the F. Water Ancylus attached to a Dyticus, &amp; the Balani attached to a Flamingo’s feet.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>With cordial thanks, pray believe me | Yours sincerely &amp; obliged | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">See the first enclosure to the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-6253.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Osbert Salvin, 20 June 1868</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">In <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6014.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Origin</hi></ref>, p. 386, CD remarked that <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3051.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Charles Lyell</ref> had told him of a <hi rend="italic">Dyticus</hi> (or <hi rend="italic">Dytiscus</hi>: a water-beetle) caught with an <hi rend="italic">Ancylus</hi> (a freshwater shell like a limpet) adhering to it. In his letter of 14 August 1863 (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 11), <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4642.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Robert Swinhoe</ref> had written to CD of a flamingo that had its legs covered with barnacles. CD was interested in possible vectors for the distribution of organisms.</note>
        </div>        
            
